author: akarasulu
msg: Changes to backend interface removed the use of the FilterExpressionTree
class using the straigt ExprNode root node instead.

author: akarasulu
msg: Changes to printing - count annotation uses BigInteger and added new
scope node for integrating base, single, and subtree level scope
constraints into the filter AST.  The AST now does not use the
FilterExpressionTree.  This class did not really do that much other
than hold the root node.  Instead we just deal with ExprNodes.  Cleaned up
filter parser a bit more preventing read blocks.

author: akarasulu
msg: Corrected branchnode toString to conditionally print scan count info if

author: akarasulu
msg: Added toString functions and fixed two major bugs in the filter parser:
the parser incorrectly used '$' instead of '&' for AND logical operator
and the FilterParserImpl class set the root ExprNode of the
FilterExpressionTree it returned to null.  These are fixed.
